{"TopicId":148696,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Swap SAS button position of radial in and out.","CreatedByName":"Rodhern","CreatedById":144074,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T13:56:57Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Rodhern","CreatedById":144074,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T13:56:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen toggling \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E on in sandbox (ver. 1.1.3) mode I get two columns of markers left of the navball.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe left column is (~) Stability Assist, \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:prograde:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/prograde3.png\u0022 title=\u0022:prograde:\u0022\u003E prograde, \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:normal:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/Normal20px.png\u0022 title=\u0022:normal:\u0022\u003E normal, \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:radial:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/Radial20px.png\u0022 title=\u0022:radial:\u0022\u003E\u003Cu\u003Eradial out\u003C/u\u003E and \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:targetpro:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/TargetPro20px.png\u0022 title=\u0022:targetpro:\u0022\u003E target.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe right column is \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:maneuver:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/Maneuver20px.png\u0022 title=\u0022:maneuver:\u0022\u003E maneuver, \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:retrograde:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/retrograde2.png\u0022 title=\u0022:retrograde:\u0022\u003E retrograde, \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:antinormal:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/Antinormal20px.png\u0022 title=\u0022:antinormal:\u0022\u003E anti-normal, \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:antiradial:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/Antiradial20px.png\u0022 title=\u0022:antiradial:\u0022\u003E\u003Cu\u003Eradial in\u003C/u\u003E and \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:targetretro:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/TargetRetro20px.png\u0022 title=\u0022:targetretro:\u0022\u003E retro-target.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a certain logic to the layout, the left column is pro-column and the right is anti-column. As such I think it would make sense if radial in and radial out swapped places with each other.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs the layout unaltered in KSP 1.2 prerelease?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat do you think about the radial in versus radial out ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T14:05:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think of radial out as radial and radial in as antiradial, the current layout makes sense to me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rodhern","CreatedById":144074,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T14:06:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222774934\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148696\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474898702\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think of radial out as radial and radial in as antiradial, the current layout makes sense to me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for the quick answer. I am convinced that you are not the only one then. In that case we better keep things as they are now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Navy2k","CreatedById":95246,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T15:03:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the sake of confusing people we should stay like we are, and because in physics there is often the right hand rule, a right hand coordinate system would put radial out as the positive part of that axis too if you put prograde as the primary coordinate which makes sense because prograde will always be prograde no matter how you define the other ones.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-26T15:10:33Z\u0022 title=\u002209/26/2016 03:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Navy2k\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}